  "title": "Federal Network Agency Local network indicators (Bundesnetzagentur)",
  "description": "[Publisher: Bundesnetzagentur] The Federal Republic of Germany is divided into 5200 local network areas. Each local area network area is assigned a two- to five-digit local area code - also called area code. The data set contains both the local network KPIs and the local network area boundaries. This is data from the Federal Network Agency. The digital boundaries of the local area network shall be published after each change in the local area network.",
